1. datasets folder at the same level as the .py files
2. create folders for each dataset inside the datasets folder (with these exact names)
    datasets
    |
    |---cifar-10
    |---faces
    |---texture
3. download links:
    cifar-10 (https://www.cs.toronto.edu/~kriz/cifar.html)
    faces (http://vis-www.cs.umass.edu/lfw/#download)
    texture (https://www.robots.ox.ac.uk/~vgg/data/dtd/)
4. cifar-10: we use data_batch_1, test_batch and batches.meta
5. faces: only extract Serena_Williams and Ariel Sharon folders
6. texture: all extraction directly in the texture folder
    only extract folders cracked, frilly and zigzaged from the images folder.
